snippet.title: Software Architecture Will Save Your Apps - MVP, MVC, MVVM, BLoC
snippet.description:
Spaghetti code. This is a nightmare of many software developers. There's nothing worse than code that is scattered everywhere without a structure. If you want to make a modification, you need to take a gazillion things into account. This way, you only ensure a slow and painful death of the whole project.

This painful style of coding also goes hand in hand with another villain of the software world - untestability. Testing code which is mixing your own logic with platform-specific code is a recipe for giving up on it completely, thus further dooming your app for premature death!

Go to my website for more information, code examples and articles:
